<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1323,1705,1891]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
A Cuban and Jamaican species (
<bibRefCitation author="Townes, H. &amp; Townes, M." box="[651,954,1705,1731]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 367" refId="ref34313" refString="Townes, H. &amp; Townes, M. (1966) A catalogue and reclassification of Neotropic Ichneumonidae. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 8, 1 - 367." type="journal article" year="1966">Townes &amp; Townes, 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld, I." box="[968,1119,1705,1731]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 309" refId="ref32773" refString="Gauld, I. (1988) A survey of the Ophioninae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) of tropical Mesoamerica with special reference to the fauna of Costa Rica. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 57, 1 - 309." type="journal article" year="1988">Gauld, 1988</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cresson, E." box="[1141,1323,1705,1731]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 200" refId="ref32037" refString="Cresson, E. (1865) On the Hymenoptera of Cuba. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 4, 1 - 200." type="journal article" year="1865">Cresson (1865)</bibRefCitation>
described the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[586,648,1745,1771]" name="Cuba" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<specimenCount box="[666,768,1745,1771]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="female">2 female</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[828,936,1745,1771]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
housed at PANS). 
<bibRefCitation author="Porter, C." box="[1163,1320,1745,1771]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="40 - 71" refId="ref33612" refString="Porter, C. (1984) Laticinctus group Thyreodon in the northern Neotropics (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Wasmann Journal of Biology, 42, 40 - 71." type="journal article" year="1984">Porter (1984)</bibRefCitation>
gave a comprehensive redescription based in the same material, and included within the species two Jamaican specimens from the BMNH, although he did it with some hesitation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1323,1705,1891]" lastBlockId="25.[264,1324,284,950]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson. Alayo" authorityYear="1973" box="[312,429,1865,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[312,429,1865,1890]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">T. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fernández-Triana Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[715,816,1865,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alayoi">
<emphasis box="[715,816,1865,1890]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">T. alayoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[831,952,1865,1890]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
T, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fernández-Triana Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[859,952,1865,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gabrieli">gabrieli</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1093,1865,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ultor">
<emphasis box="[1008,1093,1865,1890]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">T. ultor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that is the rea­ son why they have been confused or thought to be one species (but see 
<tableCitation box="[1094,1183,284,310]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="19.[264,352,565,589]" captionText="TABLE 2: Diagnosis characteristics of four related Cuban species of Thyreodon." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Table 2</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson. Alayo" authorityYear="1973" box="[1204,1323,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[1204,1323,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">T. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the lower face broader and coarser puncturae than the other species, almost forming a reticulate pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[264,1324,284,950]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<bibRefCitation author="Alayo, P." box="[312,475,404,430]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref31564" refString="Alayo, P. (1973) Catalogo de los Himenopteros de Cuba, Instituto Cubano del Libro, La Habana, 218 p." type="book" year="1973">Alayo (1973)</bibRefCitation>
cited the species in three Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[917,979,404,430]" name="Cuba" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cuba</collectingCountry>
localities: Gran Piedra and Siboney (SC) and 
<collectingRegion box="[491,641,444,470]" country="Cuba" name="Guantanamo" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Guantánamo</collectingRegion>
(GT). I have examined that material, and all specimens belong to different species: 
<taxonomicName box="[596,686,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ultor">
<emphasis box="[596,686,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">T. ultor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gran Piedra specimens), 
<taxonomicName authority="Fernández-Triana Table Of Contents, 2005" authorityName="Fernández-Triana Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[1003,1106,484,509]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alayoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1003,1106,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">T. alayoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1116,1208,484,510]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Siboney specimen) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fernández-Triana Table Of Contents, 2005" authorityName="Fernández-Triana Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[442,563,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gabrieli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[442,563,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">T. gabrieli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[570,661,524,550]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<collectingRegion box="[675,827,524,550]" country="Cuba" name="Guantanamo" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Guantánamo</collectingRegion>
specimen).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[264,1324,284,950]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Because of misidentifications, it is really difficult to be sure about distribution of the species in 
<collectingCountry box="[387,452,604,630]" name="Cuba" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, especially without the study of specimens housed at 
<collectingCountry box="[1087,1146,604,630]" name="United States of America" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">USA</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1205,1251,604,630]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">UK</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gundlach, J." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref33012" refString="Gundlach, J. (1886) Contribucion a la entomologia cubana. Tomo II. Hymenopteros, La Habana, 187 pp." type="book" year="1886">Gundlach (1886)</bibRefCitation>
stated he had collected the species troughtout the all country. 
<bibRefCitation author="Townes, H. &amp; Townes, M." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 367" refId="ref34313" refString="Townes, H. &amp; Townes, M. (1966) A catalogue and reclassification of Neotropic Ichneumonidae. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 8, 1 - 367." type="journal article" year="1966">Townes &amp; Townes (1966)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned three Cuban localities for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson. Alayo" authorityYear="1973" box="[894,1013,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[894,1013,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">T. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Nueva Gerona (WC, IJ), 
<collectingRegion box="[264,470,724,750]" country="Cuba" name="Santiago de Cuba" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Santiago de Cuba</collectingRegion>
(EC, SC) and 
<collectingRegion box="[640,789,724,750]" country="Cuba" name="Guantanamo" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Guantánamo</collectingRegion>
(EC, GT). 
<bibRefCitation author="Porter, C." box="[918,1074,724,750]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="294 - 304" refId="ref33673" refString="Porter, C. (1989) A new Floridan Athyreodon Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae) with comments on related species of the northern Neotropics. Florida Entomologist, 72, 294 - 304." type="journal article" year="1989">Porter (1989)</bibRefCitation>
studied the 
<typeStatus box="[1215,1322,724,750]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">lectotype</typeStatus>
and two other Cuban specimens at PANS, but he did not provided information about localities. I have only seen one authenticated specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson. Alayo" authorityYear="1973" box="[886,1004,804,829]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Thyreodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis box="[886,1004,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">T. grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Cuban collections, from Western 
<collectingCountry box="[367,432,844,870]" name="Cuba" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, but for any reason Alayo did not mention it on his Catalogue.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
